issue.title: Use generic rather than release specific link in exclude lists

repository.name: openj9-openjdk-jdk
repository.description: Extensions for OpenJDK for Eclipse OpenJ9

issue.body:
In the exclude lists for the `OpenJCEPlusFIPS` weak and strict profile, a generic link is provided for each excluded test until it is investigated. Since the solution will become available for all releases, no release specific link is required.

Signed-off-by: Kostas Tsiounis <kostas.tsiounis@ibm.com>

issue.title: Update the FIPS140-3 strict profile test exclude list

repository.name: openj9-openjdk-jdk17
repository.description: Extensions for OpenJDK 17 for Eclipse OpenJ9

issue.body:
In the FIPS 140-3 strict profile test exclude list, the test case name `TLSWontNegotiateDisabledCipherAlgos.java` should be updated to include the test ID.

This change applies only to JDK 17. JDK 11 doesn't have this test, and JDK 21 and later versions have already added this test to the FIPS 140-3 strict profile exclude list.
